'''Valentine Werier''', {{Post-nominals|country=CAN|CM|OM}} (June 29, 1917 â€“ April 22, 2014) was a Canadian journalist for the ''[[Winnipeg Free Press]]''. Werier was honoured with the [[Order of Manitoba]] in 2004<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mhs.mb.ca/docs/people/orderofmanitoba.shtml|title=Members of the Order of Manitoba|publisher=Mhs.mb.ca|accessdate=2014-04-27}}</ref> and the [[Order of Canada]]. He was born in Winnipeg in 1917.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mhs.mb.ca/docs/people/werier_v.shtml|title=Memorable Manitobans: Valentine "Val" Werier (1917-2014)|website=Mhs.mb.ca|accessdate=26 December 2018}}</ref>

Werier died at the age of 96 on April 22, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/national/order-of-canada-journalist-val-werier-dies-at-age-96/article18121142/|title=Order of Canada journalist Val Werier dies at age 96 |website=Theglobeandmail.com|date=2014-04-22|accessdate=2014-04-27}}</ref>

